<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Burden2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Burden</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Burthen,</orth> vb., 1) to load; a) absol. <cit><quote>overborne with --ing grief,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 10</bibl></cit>. b) trans.: <cit><quote>the colt that's backed and --ed being young,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 419" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 419</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wild music --s every bough,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 102.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 102, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.203" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.320" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 320</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 23</bibl>. Followed by <emph>with</emph>: <cit><quote>b. our remembrance with a heaviness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 199</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 36</bibl>.<lb />2) to charge: <cit><quote>this is false he --s me withal,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 209</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 209</bibl>

